		<li class="alt" id="comment-22978">
			<div class="comment-number">167</div>
			<cite>Shafe</cite> Says:
						<br />

			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="http://depletedcranium.com/?p=5322&amp;cp=4#comment-22978" title="">March 29th, 2010 at 3:51 am</a> </small>

			<div class="quoter-wrap">
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="http://depletedcranium.com/why-you-cant-build-a-bomb-from-spent-fuel/#comment-22970"><b>Lantzelot said:</b></a></p>
<blockquote cite="http://depletedcranium.com/why-you-cant-build-a-bomb-from-spent-fuel/#comment-22970"><p>
So it is a global &#8220;problem&#8221; and it has been around for a long time. A language is not a static thing and you may see this as part of the evolution of it, accept it and go with the flow (it doesn&#8217;t mean that you have to write like that yourself).<br />
Or you can try to fight it by calling for better (stricter?) language education, and pointing it out every time that you encounter the phenomena. But it will be a battle that you will lose. So if you decide to join the Dodo and the T-Rex, at least try to do it with a smile, and be amused about the new ways that your cherished language is changing.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<p>I can&#8217;t seem to express my disagreement with your comment without writing a thesis, so let me just say, &#8220;I disagree.&#8221;</p>
<p>There&#8217;s no need to accept laziness and ignorance, and I will always reject:</p>
<p>-Improper construction, e.g. irregardless, ironical</p>
<p>-Homophone confusion, e.g. there, their, they&#8217;re; two, to, too.  (sorry Steve)</p>
<p>-Saying &#8220;in lieu of&#8221; when you mean &#8220;in light of&#8221;</p>
<p>-Going slow when the sign says &#8220;stop&#8221;</p>
<p>-Amputating my right hand when the problem is in my left.</p>
<p>Wrong is wrong, and popularity does not make any of these right.</p>
<br><a href="http://depletedcranium.com/why-you-cant-build-a-bomb-from-spent-fuel/quote-comment-22978/#comment" onclick="commentQuote('22978','I can\'t seem to express my disagreement with your comment without writing a thesis, so let me just say, &quot;I disagree.&quot;\n\nThere\'s no need to accept laziness and ignorance, and I will always reject:\n\n-Improper construction, e.g. irregardless, ironical\n\n-Homophone confusion, e.g. there, their, they\'re; two, to, too.  (sorry Steve)\n\n-Saying &quot;in lieu of&quot; when you mean &quot;in light of&quot;\n\n-Going slow when the sign says &quot;stop&quot;\n\n-Amputating my right hand when the problem is in my left.\n\nWrong is wrong, and popularity does not make any of these right.','comment');return false;" title="Quote this comment" class="quoter_comment" rel="nofollow">Quote Comment</a>		</li>

	
	
