It seems possible that there is classified knowledge of an efficient way to reprocess reactor wastes to extract relatively pure Pu239.  If so, fear that that knowledge may leak out (or be independently rediscovered) might explain some of the conflicting information we&#8217;re seeing.</p>
<p>BTW, it&#8217;s not too hard to show that a device with plutonium chemically refined from reactor waste *will* pre-initiate.  That doesn&#8217;t seem to be disputed.  The controversy seems to be over how much yield can be achieved despite pre-initiation.</p>
